类 LazyStreams

    • magicbook.gtlitecore.api.utils.stream.LazyStreams

  • public final class LazyStreams
extends java.lang.Object
    A lazy and short-circuit stream related utilities class, this class is based on common stream and StreamEx, provided some methods to reduce same code usage.

      • fastSortedByKey

        public static <K,V> java.util.List<K> fastSortedByKey(java.util.Map<K,V> map,
                                                      java.util.function.ToIntFunction<? super V> tierExtractor)
        Generated a sorted list for a given map.

        The action of values is from tierExtractor, it is used to send value to the sorter. As default, tier value used integer type.

        类型参数:
        K - The type of key of map.
        V - The type of value of map.
        参数:
        map - A common map.
        tierExtractor - A to-integer function to get the value which will be sent to sorter of the list.
        返回:
        Sorted new list of all key values in map with the action which contained in sorter by value values in entry map of map.

      • fastSortedByKey

        public static <K,V> java.util.List<K> fastSortedByKey(it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.objects.AbstractObject2ObjectMap<K,V> map)
        Generated a sorted list for a given map.
        类型参数:
        K - The type of key of map.
        V - The type of value of map.
        参数:
        map - A it.unimi.dsi.fastutil.objects.Object2ObjectMap, for example, we used Object2ObjectOpenHashMap as the default choice of storage usage in GTLiteAPI.
        返回:
        Sorted new list of all key values in map with the action which contained in sorter by value values in entry map of map.
        抛出:
        java.lang.ClassCastException - When the correspondenced types of MetaBlock at <K> is not the implementation of WrappedIntTier.
        另请参阅:
        AbstractObject2ObjectMap

      • gatherer

        public static <T,A,R> java.util.stream.Stream<R> gatherer(java.util.stream.Stream<T> source,
                                                          Gatherer<? super T,A,R> gatherer)
        Returns a stream consisting of the results of applying the given Gatherer of the upstream source to the elements of this stream.

        This is a stateful intermediate operation that is an extension point.

        Gatherers are highly flexible and can describe a vast array of possibly stateful operations, with support for short-circuiting, and parallelization.

        When executed in parallel, multiple intermediate results may be instantiated, populated, and merged to maintain isolation of mutable data structures. Therefore, even when executed in parallel with non-thread-safe data structures (such as a ArrayList), no additional synchronization is needed for a parallel reduction.

        类型参数:
        T - The type of input elements for the gatherer.
        A - The type of the state of the returned initializer.
        R - The type of results for the gatherer.
        参数:
        source - Upstream for gatherer pipeline.
        gatherer - A gatherer.
        返回:
        The new stream.
